Here are both approaches for .NET MAUI Shell navigation:

**1. Passing a simple string (Product ID):**

```csharp
// ProductListPage.xaml.cs or ViewModel
async void OnProductTapped(Product product)
{
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"{nameof(ProductDetailsPage)}?productId={product.Id}");
}
```

**2. Passing a complex object:**

```csharp
// Pass the full Product object via navigation parameters dictionary
async void OnProductTapped(Product product)
{
    var navParams = new Dictionary<string, object>
    {
        { "product", product }
    };
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync(nameof(ProductDetailsPage), navParams);
}
```

**Receiving both on the ViewModel with `IQueryAttributable`:**

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach 1: simple string parameter
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service if needed
            _ = LoadProductAsync(ProductId);
        }

        // Approach 2: full object passed via dictionary
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }

    private async Task LoadProductAsync(string id)
    {
        Product = await _productService.GetByIdAsync(id);
    }
}
```

**Route registration (MauiProgram.cs or AppShell):**

```csharp
Routing.RegisterRoute(nameof(ProductDetailsPage), typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
```

**Key differences:**

| | String param | Object param |
|---|---|---|
| Method | URI query string | `Dictionary<string, object>` overload |
| Received as | `object` → call `.ToString()` | `object` → cast to your type |
| Survives serialization | Yes (deep-link safe) | No (in-memory only) |

Use the string approach for deep-linking support; use the object approach when you already have the data in memory and want to avoid an extra lookup.
